com.google.template.soy.sharedpasses.render

Class EvalVisitor

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.google.template.soy.basetree.AbstractReturningNodeVisitor<ExprNode,R>
      • com.google.template.soy.exprtree.AbstractReturningExprNodeVisitor<SoyValue>
        • com.google.template.soy.sharedpasses.render.EvalVisitor
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    NodeVisitor<ExprNode,SoyValue>

    public class EvalVisitor
extends AbstractReturningExprNodeVisitor<SoyValue>
    Visitor for evaluating the expression rooted at a given ExprNode.

    Important: Do not use outside of Soy code (treat as superpackage-private).

    AbstractReturningNodeVisitor.exec(N) may be called on any expression. The result of evaluating the expression (in the context of the data and env passed into the constructor) is returned as a SoyValue object.

        protected SoyValue computeFunctionHelper(SoyJavaFunction fn,

                                         FunctionNode fnNode)
        Protected helper for computeFunction. This helper exists so that subclasses can override it.
        Parameters:
        fn - The function object.
        args - The arguments to the function.
